Think about activiatng through the core to support the lumbar spine as you raise your legs to a V shape

This is a challenging core strengthening movement as we take away stabilty to add workload for the abdominals
Take away support hands and reach toward the toes to challenge further

If youre tight in your hamstrings or lower back, you may wish to modify (use hands support if back is tight as you are asking a lot of the abs to keep torso upright. Slight bend at the knee if hamstring tight)

data.Rule description: Class plans should comprise betwen 8 and 12 movements for an hour long class
8 movements for beginner to intermediate, 12 for advancecd
Beginners should do mostly L1 and L2 in the movements and the Pilates app daily session narratives categorise beginner and advanved movements very well
Class movements should be fresh and Pilates instructors should review prior classes to avoid overuse of certain movements
Movements within a class should avoid consecutive overuse of muscles so lookbacks should be done to safeguard against this
Transitions should avoid discomfort between movements
Warm ups and cool downs should relate to movement muscle groups used during the class stage
All class structures should follow the structure highlighted in the categories and subcategories columns in sheet "CH Class history - detail"
Scrape the Internet for home care advice. Best sources are american school of medicine as well as other medically accedited institutions. Advice should be accessible though
Movements should be avoided if the student is injured and movement relates to an injured part of student's body
Pregnant women must not use the app as some movements may prove harmful. Advise attending human-led instructor courses
